%% 04 Document management | Detailed NodeJS/Core flow
flowchart TB
  A[Web document request with user JWT] --> B[Require ACTIVE account and current authVersion]
  B --> C{Role and ownership}
  C -->|ADMIN| D[Manage every document]
  C -->|TEACHER| E[Manage only documents uploaded by the current user]
  C -->|STUDENT| F[Document Management API is forbidden]
  D --> G{Requested operation}
  E --> G

  G -->|List| H[Search, filter and paginate documents]
  G -->|Detail| I[Read metadata and latest processing job]
  G -->|Update metadata| J{Only title changes?}
  G -->|Open original file| K[Authorize and stream through NodeJS]
  G -->|Hide, unhide or delete| L[Continue in flow 05]

  J -->|Yes| M[Update title without reprocessing]
  J -->|No, file content changes| N[Upload a new document through flow 01]
  H --> O[Return public DTO without storage_key]
  I --> O
  M --> O
  K --> P[Resolve storage_key internally and never expose it]

  N1[DELETED documents are excluded from normal lists]
  N2[Pagination uses normalized offset and limit, maximum 100]
